Scott: Right?

978
01:02:58,776 --> 01:02:59,820
Scott: Magazines as a thing.

979
01:03:01,091 --> 01:03:06,340
Scott: So, yeah, magazine, you know, September is a magazine half-month.

980
01:03:07,020 --> 01:03:07,244
Rym: Highlights?

981
01:03:07,264 --> 01:03:08,360
Rym: Sports Illustrated for Kids?

982
01:03:09,342 --> 01:03:09,705
Scott: Yeah.

983
01:03:10,390 --> 01:03:11,620
Scott: With regular Sports Illustrated.

984
01:03:12,080 --> 01:03:17,420
Rym: Yeah, I read the... Sports Illustrated for Kids, when we get to that show, was fucking better than Sports Illustrated.

985
01:03:18,641 --> 01:03:20,400
Scott: I mean, Teen Vogue is better than Vogue.

986
01:03:20,520 --> 01:03:22,669
Rym: Teen Vogue is, like, consistently better.

987
01:03:22,729 --> 01:03:25,200
Rym: Teen Vogue is shockingly a great magazine.

988
01:03:25,760 --> 01:03:28,760
Scott: Teen Vogue might be the best magazine that exists now.

989
01:03:28,840 --> 01:03:34,100
Rym: Like, if you think we're joking, like, we are so not joking about Teen Vogue.

